==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Herculean
<hw>Her*cu"le*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>herculeus</ets>, fr. <ets>Hercules</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>hercul⟦eacute⟧en</ets>. See <er>Hercules</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Requiring the strength of Hercules; hence, very
great, difficult, or dangerous; <as>as, an <ex>Herculean</ex>
task</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having extraordinary strength or size; <as>as,
<ex>Herculean</ex> limbs</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Herculean</xex>
Samson.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hercules</ent>⟦br⟧
